message.content: Since the drying rate is not specified, we can only assume that all 10 pairs of socks dried in 10 hours due to the weather conditions. If we apply the same conditions to 7 pairs of socks, it would take approximately 7 hours for them to dry (assuming the drying rate is proportional to the number of socks). However, this is an approximation and actual drying times could vary based on factors like humidity, wind speed, and the material of the socks.
